**Key framing I led with:** Today sits inside a rare convergence window — it's **FOMC Day 1** (decision tomorrow, Jun 17, the **first meeting under new Chair Kevin Warsh** + dot plot), the **start of the triple-witch T-3→T-1 strongest-edge window** (Jun 16–18), with **Triple Witch + S&P rebalance Friday** and **Russell reconstitution Jun 26** ahead. Pulled from CALENDAR.md.

**Highlights:**
- **Tape:** Risk-on relief rally — oil down ~3% on the US-Iran deal, soft DXY, stable yields, green tech futures, VIX 16 (normal). Bias: cautiously constructive, but capped ahead of the Fed.
- **Movers:** Flagged the 4 watchlist names in the >3% movers (OLN, MU, MNTS, TLS) plus news-driven ANET and LMT. SPCX +7.53% on IPO mania.
- **Watchlist:** No Tier 1 name moved >3% and no earnings today, so I leaned on RSI extremes — **LDOS RSI 23 (deeply oversold)**, FTNT 72 / PANW 67 (extended), and the lagging Space infra names diverging from SpaceX euphoria.
- **Catalysts:** Cross-referenced thesis files (SpaceX IPO mid-2026, NVIDIA Rubin, Vistra-Meta nuclear deliveries, lithium >$20K validation).

**Discipline notes:** All six economic releases marked **Pending** (none had printed at the 11:38 PT collection). I flagged the two data anomalies (Brent, LDOS) and the FRED timeout (2Y is a prior-close print) rather than smoothing them over. Every number traces to the briefing file with source attribution.
